caption: Food is okay but overpriced. The calamari was excellent but the pepper steak wasn't as impressive as I think they would lead you to believe. I don't think the quality and price are in alignment though many consider this to be a top tier restaraunt in anchorage.

Atmosphere was nice. Waitress was also nice but not overly friendly; during the only brief conversations, each time we had she abruptly stopped and said that she had to go so other things. The food was the most lackluster of our time in AK. My lamb lollipops were lukewarm and I believe that the charcuterie board was the first we’ve ever not finished. Luckily, the wine was good.

A dining delight! Saturday lunch at Jens' was fabulous. The service was friendly and efficient. The food was divine. My choice of pink peppered Kodiak scallops with fennel, roasted Brussels sprouts and polenta was beautiful, the flavors combined in harmony. My date's choice of pistachio crusted rockfish was delish, served with a mango-jalepeño burre blanc, rice and veg. Will we go back? Yes!

Everything was very good, The Wellington was not a traditional Wellington, I have eaten many in other states, The flavor was good but I would rather have it without the biscuit on top and the dough around it. Its more like a filet with a biscuit instead of a beef wellington. It was unnecessary. I will definitely go back though, excellent service and flavor. Best Calamari I have eaten.

I had one experience here many years ago. Nasty food served by nasty people. Don't know if it's gotten any better, but I'll never return to find out. The head chef coming to my table to insult me and my wife, telling us we didn't know what good food was, ended any chance of redemption from this pretentious greasy spoon.
This place is amazing!  The service and atmosphere will definitely keep me coming back. The food was so delicious and we had to have desert!
Our go-to spot for special occasions. Danish cuisine with an Alaskan twist. The meals never disappoint.

Great place for a nice dinner, fresh Halibut prepared with mushrooms and a creme sauce, fresh steamed vegetables. Wouldn't change a thing! Service is wonderful, staff is friendly and accommodating. Would recommend for date night or a night out of delicious food or dessert.  recommend for lunch and dinner

Their service was great for how busy they were. They told us things may come out slow because their kitchen was backed up, but I was actually impressed with how quick everything came out! Be prepared for a long wait though...we waited over an hour, but it was worth the wait. Not sure if it was because it was two day's before New Year's Eve or what, but I'd recommend to plan accordingly when coming here.
Met a friend for drink and appetizer; been too long. Service outstanding, no better oysters, and perfect salads. Always  treated like family.
We always try to stop in here at least one meal when we come up to the lake camping. The food is always good, actually it's great. The service is friendly and welcoming

It is a quite place, off the beaten path. If you have not found this place to try you should. The appetizer was well displayed and went well with the wine. For the main dish it was outstanding. I had the ribeye with a steak sauce that was outstanding. The wife had the ahi tuna dish with peanut sauce and she enjoyed it tremendously. Not sure if it is due to the pandemic for the more romantic, cozy atmosphere but I loved this place.
Amazing food, and super friendly staff!!

Exceptional food and extraordinary service.....my friend and I enjoyed three meals (six entree’s)during our stay in Anchorage......all prepared for takeout at our request.....best find ever....Excellent fried steak and gravy and a very good Greek salad. Outstanding service by Kimberly. Good wine list. Easy parking
The food was spectacular! The waitress was so great! It was overall one of the best experiences here in Anchorage!! Would highly recommend!

This is a wonderful restaurant that caters mostly to adults! The food is truly divine!!!! My husband ordered the Murrati's Köfte (Greek meatballs with seasoned rice and salad on the side) and everything was delicious! The meatballs were so flavorful and tender, the rice had a light, fluffy texture with amazing seasonings and the salad was a garden salad with a citrusy/olive oil blend dressing and some spices.
First time trying out this place today and I loved it.  Service was amazing. Place is clean and welcoming.  Food and desserts were delicious.  Definitely coming back 4 more.
It was underwhelming. Food was under seasoned and, frankly, bland. Well cooked and unnecessarily large portions. I really wouldn't recommend it. It's "okay".

A small restaurant with 5 star food and service. A fine dining restaurant in Anchorage with a very good selection of seafood and meat choices, as well as salads, soups and desserts. Lots of parking on site and a highly recommended restaurant.

They also have a nice selection of wines to choose from & can recommend the best to pair with your meal. They’re peppered steak is hands-down one of the best dishes on the menu and everything else on the menu is delicious as well. Lastly, if you love dessert like I do, then you definitely need to try their carrot cake! It’s one of the best desserts you’ll ever have!

The server also gave him his plate back but failed to give him his fork back (she cleaned off our table, at least the water refill was persistent) could of made better food at home or at a cheaper restaurant.

If anyone rates this restaurant bellow 5 stars they are lying through their teeth. Not cheap, be prepared to drop a pretty penny. However the entrees present some of the best flavor combinations and presentations in the City. Do not pass this place up.

Jen's is one of my favorites because it's an upper class Ambience at a middle class price range. I go there for 2 things only. The calamari from the appetizer menu for $17.50 and coffee. The calamari has to be the absolute best I've ever had. It's not breaded it's served with a lemony sauce and capers, along with toasted triangles which blend wonderfully with the leftover sauce. This is the only place I found where the calamari it's not breaded and I cannot overstate that it is the best I've ever enjoyed. It's my Friday night go to Restaurant. I will add that there wine list is impressive as well. call for reservations or you can enjoy eating in the entry bar area which is very nice as well before 5 p.m.

The most amazing meal! Impeccable customer service and lovely quiet setting! The beet and barley salad was "to die for" and the chicken fried steak was tender, flavorful and delicious. Best meal I've had in Anchorage!

Don't let the strip mall intimidate you.  This place serves from-scratch food that is of high quality, beaming with flavor and very creative.  You must give Jens' a try.  We just moved to Anchorage and are exploring the restaurant scene and boy are we glad we found Jens'.  I had the seafood crepe made with high quality melt-in-your mouth seafood and a rich cream sauce with just the right amount of rosemary and sherry.  My husband ordered the Cajun style cod served with a house made Cajun dipping sauce that was outstanding.  We both started with an excellent creamy mushroom soup and ended our lunch with their from-scratch red berry pudding with cream, very refreshing. You will find the restaurant classy yet casual, white linens, high quality tableware and fresh flowers at each table.  Our GPS brought us around the back side of the building so be aware.  We can't wait to go back for dinner for their pepper steak and a glass of wine.

The menu changes frequently, and there is something for everyone.  I applaud their daily vegetarian offerings.  Our server was professional, understated, didn't ask any inane questions about our day--perfect.  The quality of food is uncompromising, but expect to pay for it. The bar area is pleasant, but the dining room is stodgy and decorated in a disturbing great-grandmother pink.  The plastic flowers on the table add to the creepiness of the dining room.

Excellent dinner choices, all wild Alaska fish, perfectly prepared. Our waitress Mariah took great care of us for our anniversary celebration. Bellissima!

Got mine Togo after taking 2 bites. 2 blocks down I gave it to a homeless man who smelled then threw it in the trash. You can get better food from Long John Silvers. Payed $40 for some fish with squirt sauce on top. Service was good! Went to burger stop down the road. Delicious!!
Delicious food, lovely atmosphere,  excellent service. A great place for a special occasion!

Food and service are excellent. Selections are interesting, unique and wonderfully rendered. Anchorage has many wonderful restaurants, but few meet and none exceed Jen's standards of quality and appeal.

I ALWAYS read reviews, so I thought it would only be right to leave one to help others out. Today is my husbands birthday, and this place was NOTHING SHORT of making it special. I am BEYOND picky... but EVERYTHING we had was good. They close the kitchen at 10, we arrived at 9:52, and they STILL allowed us to dine there. That was the first plus( & not once were they snooty or rushing us because of the time) the waiter was super friendly and very attentive. Our food was cooked quickly... another plus, and it wasn't half done. It was still cooked to our liking. I'm usually hard on my reviews, but I give this place 5+ stars. They were pretty pricey, but I didnt expect anything less because, of course, I read the other reviews, lol and I expected it anyway(because I figure it was a "classy" type of place). But I didnt mind because it was for my husband. And I thought the portions were worth the price, it was enough to fill us up. So I was happy about it, over all. We will more than likely return here before we leave alaska and I would recommend it to others as well... Oh yea... and we were there at 11:04(after closing) and the waiter didnt even mind taking our pictures. They made tonight perfect for my husband and I'm happy about it.

One of the finest dining restaurants in Anchorage.  Jens' Restaurant can be difficult to find, but I think that makes it more desirable. I am SO settled on this restaurant. I love it. Time after time they achieve excellence while most other restaurants in Anchorage are like going to a food lottery, a service lottery and a stupid-excuse-from-the-manager lottery where I have to sit through the latest cockamamie story from their managers explaining that the fish IS "fresh" you know... it was fresh when it was frozen, or, yes, she has worked in an indoor restaurant before, or mussels aren't supposed to be open, or they're not really drunk, it's just their personalities, or "try them SAVanons, 'cause they're good but they're CHEAP, etc.. The other places are good one time, horrible the next, etc. Our little dining group is slowly working our way through the menu at Jen's and we haven't been disappointed yet by any of our selections. This week I celebrated my birthday at Jen's specifically because of their consistency out of hundreds of restaurants to choose from and again, it was absolutely perfect. The "house" salad is a silly name however when it shows up with numerous types of greens, assorted nuts, cheese, sliced strawberries and a dozen other ingredients. I think "spectacular" salad would be a better name. We had lamb... perfect, Black Cod... perfect, Charcuterie ... perfect, and I have forgotten what the fourth meal was because by the time my dinner arrived I was so excited that I didn't notice anything else until dessert arrived. And again... perfect. I don't know why I put up with some of the other restaurants in town for so many years. I guess that I just really wanted them to be good but they kept letting me down. Jen's is absolutely a treasure and I like every single thing about the restaurant, and not the least of these is that I can actually hear the conversations of the people that I'm dining with. If I could change anything about this restaurant I would move it to a really cute house on a lake, maybe, but then it would probably take me months to get a reservation, so I don't think that I would change even this detail. Life's too short to eat bad food or to be served by an idiot, I'm done abusing myself. In the future I'm going to Jen's or Marx Bros and that's it.

Pepper steak is to die for, and you can order it for lunch or dinner! It's like cutting into butter and just melts in your mouth! When I want seafood I usually order the halibut. Love the mushrooms and the  beurre blanc sauce. Have enjoyed many fashions of scallops, rockfish, salmon and cod with different sauces the chef creates. Absolutely the nicest place for New Year's Eve dinner, including champagne, appetizers, duck black-eyed pea soup and choice of delights such as beef tenderloin topped with shallot butter over cabernet-braised wild mushrooms, king crab crepes or ahi tuna. The dessert is spectacular every year, and always different, but is almost always too beautiful a creation to eat! My favorite was the chocolate martini glass!! And with a complimenting wine and beer list, it truly is my favorite special place for dinner!
Have had dinner here several times. Their eatery has a great philosophy of farm to table and it shows in their selections. The elk was awesome. Highly recommended if it's on the special menu.
Jens is awesome and one of the best places to eat in Anchorage!
Absolute amazing! I love to come to Jens restaurant, then i was on exchange in Alaska it was the place i felt mostly at home! Thanks to Jens and he's wife for being so kind! :-)
Excellent place to eat.  Very high quality.  Space is somewhat small, cozy.

First of all I arrived 30 minutes before opening time on Saturday (didn't look at a clock, belly said eat) and the folks said not to worry that they would take care of me.  Shortly after setting down the place filled up in no time flat with others thinking like me, mealtime. The service was that of what a restaurant should be and then some, my waiter knew about every item on the menu with great detail. I had Oysters Rockefeller for a starter, and lamb for the main dish.... oh what a treat. The only downside is my belly is smaller then the menu of some of my favorite dishes, which will make Jen's a regular stop for me when traveling thru Anchorage for some time now. Being a good cook myself I must say that this Restaurant passes my pickiness when it comes to a great meal. One may think the food is a bit pricey but for a person that dines out often when traveling, I will have to say it is only a few dollars more, making it money well spent.
